narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Analyzing Southeast Asian history through a number of different types of sources. Enhanced ability to maximize the value of primary source material in research.
History of Southeast Asia from the colonial period onwards, and with focuses on different aspects of society.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Class material was very interesting. Readings were at a manageable and fair amount. Section and discussion times were a bit too disorganized due to the low number of students in the class. I hope that there will be more efforts in the future to promote this class before hand to create more structure.

It provides a very good survey of a number of interesting and important topics, but I feel that a separate section would have been more useful because it would give students time to think and process new information before discussing.
Material was interesting and the topics given for the papers were well chosen. However, sometimes the class would go past the time it was supposed to end.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes I would recommend this course to a student. There is too high a shortage of Southeast Asian classes taught at this school. This class provides a nice foundation to build up knowledge in the field, especially when you have no prior knowledge to start with.
Yes if you are interested in the region.
